Ad [Addendum] 32. Witt Library. Bird's Nest: 1) Vienna [...] Exh.Antw. 1930, Flem.Exh.RA 1927, N° 228. The catal.says: A drawing, reproducing this composition in the Uffizi is dated 1564 or 1560, 23 x 27in. (58 x 69); 2) P2 Wagner Sale, Christie 16.I.1925, N° 153, panel 23 x 29 1/2in. gives complete composition with ? on right and flowers pyramidal roofs on left and right; [verso] Roundel Holburne Museums, Bath also to be note also ad 61. Original. Another composition repeated in roundel.
